'''Lisa Nehus Saxon''' (born October 28, 1959 in California) is an American sports writer.

While working for the [[Daily News of Los Angeles]] from 1979 until 1987, Saxon became one of the first women to cover [[Major League Baseball]] for a daily newspaper.  While fighting for women to gain equal access to press boxes and [[locker rooms]], Saxon endured both verbal and physical abuse.<ref>https://sports.vice.com/en_us/article/lisa-saxon-the-woman-who-helped-change-sports-writing-forever</ref><ref>http://www.newsday.com/sports/columnists/barbara-barker/journalist-dealt-with-harassment-opened-doors-for-other-women-1.9644552</ref>

